              <h3>Summary</h3>

              <p>The QUICC (Quarterly Indicator of Cover Change) product was developed at NASA Ames Research Center by the CASA ecosystem modeling team. QUICC is based on a comparison of the MODIS Global Vegetation Index (VI) images at the exact same time period each year (end of March, June, September and December) in consecutive years and detects areas of major  landcover change (not just forest). The CASA team updates the global QUICC products as soon as the newest quarterly MODIS worldwide VI image at 5-km spatial resolution is available.</p>

